Reports
Lightning Report Builder is a powerful tool for analyzing your Salesforce data. Group, filter, and summarize records to answer business questions.
REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To create, edit, and delete reports in private folders: Create and Customize Reports
To create, edit, and delete reports in public and private folders: Report Builder OR Report Builder (Lightning Experience)
On the Analytics tab, select Create | Report, or on the Reports tab, click New Report.
Choose a report type, and click Start Report.
Create New Report window:
Select a category from the left panel and search for report types by name.
Filter by objects or fields.
Fields included via lookup or part of composite fields arenâ€™t available as filter options.
Add a column to your report: choose a field in the Add column dropdown.
Remove a column from your report: click .
Summarize a column: select  | Summarize, and choose how you want to summarize.
Group records: choose a field in the Add group dropdown.
Hide detail rows, subtotals, and grand total by clicking switches at the bottom of the preview pane.
Un-group records: find the group and click , or from the Groups list, click .
Filter records: click .
Add a field filter: choose a field from the Add filter dropdown.
Remove a filter: click the  on the filter.
Add a chart: first add at least one group, and click Add Chart.
Customize the chart by clicking .
Save the report. Give it a name and description, and save in an appropriate folder.
Click Run to view report results.
